(20, 'PHP5', 'How Googleâ€™s Bad Data Wiped a Neighborhood off the Map', 'manaor', '2019-03-19 05:55:43', 'upload/loginPage.png', '<p name=\"de54\" id=\"de54\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--hasDropCapModel graf--hasDropCap graf--hasDropCapImage graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0px; clear: left; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">nnette Lott sat through the meeting with studied patience, waiting for the moment city officials would open the floor and she could ask them about Google Maps.</p><p name=\"deaf\" id=\"deaf\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">It was late spring in Buffalo, New York, in 2015 â€” a season that was unusually hot that year, and heated. The wood-paneled meeting room at Gethsemane Grape Street Baptist Church hummed with anxious homeowners from Buffaloâ€™s Fruit Belt neighborhood, where a burgeoning, billion-dollar medical complex threatened to displace them.</p><p name=\"c6d7\" id=\"c6d7\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Poor folks had called the Fruit Belt home for more than 150 years â€” first German immigrants, then African-Americans. Lottâ€™s parents bought their pale turquoise two-story house in 1955, moving north from Bluefield, West Virginia, to help build up a community that would become the heart of Buffaloâ€™s black working class.</p><p name=\"270d\" id=\"270d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Now that community was under threat â€” or so it seemed to Lott. The 66-year-old had Googled directions to her neighborhood and found that the app had changed the name of her community from the â€œFruit Beltâ€ to something called â€œMedical Park.â€</p>', 'Now that community was under threat', 0, 'Published'),
(21, 'JAVA', 'Lott learned that the issue had been festering for years', 'manaor', '2019-03-19 05:57:08', 'upload/Untitled-1.jpg', '<p name=\"04e5\" id=\"04e5\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin-top: 38px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Lott learned that the issue had been festering for years, and she wanted answers. The 2,300 residents in the Fruit Belt didnâ€™t refer to the community as â€œMedical Park,â€ but Google Maps had done so since the late 2000s. Community members argued the designation was a calculated tweak in favor of gentrification, a digital rechristening that would be used to sell houses, market Airbnbs, and wrest the neighborhoodâ€™s future from the people who had made a home there for generations.</p><p name=\"3ba8\" id=\"3ba8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Lott didnâ€™t know it at the time, but the misnomer also revealed a great deal about the invisible process major tech firms use to put neighborhoods on their maps â€” and how decisions based off arcane data sets can affect y.</p><p name=\"90cc\" id=\"90cc\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Who erased the Fruit Belt? Lott demanded of officials. What the hell is Medical Park? And how did it get on this map?</p><p name=\"4c2c\" id=\"4c2c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-indent: -0.4em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">â€œThere is nobody in City Hall who would dare utter the phrase Medical Park anywhere near the Fruit Belt,â€ Brendan Mehaffy, the cityâ€™s chief planner, told me recently. â€œSo I really canâ€™t tell you how this happened.â€</p>', 'communities thousands of miles awa', 0, 'Published'),
(22, 'JAVASCRIPT', 'But unbeknownst even to city officials', 'manoar', '2019-03-19 05:57:51', 'upload/gig images for abul hasan vai.jpg', '<p name=\"8a00\" id=\"8a00\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--hasDropCapModel graf--hasDropCap graf--hasDropCapImage graf--leading\" style=\"margin-top: 38px; margin-bottom: 0px; clear: left; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">he Fruit Belt was quiet on a recent weekday, hushed under a slick of wet snow. A lone man walked in the street, his hands stuffed into his coat pockets, never checking for cars as he crossed the road.</p><p name=\"1667\" id=\"1667\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Fewer people live in the neighborhood now than did even two or three decades ago. And signs of contraction abound: a boarded-up storefront with its shingled roof caved in; a scattershot of empty lots amidst dense houses and gardens. Meanwhile, just west of the Fruit Belt and across Michigan Street, every year the Medical Campus adds new labs, offices, incubators, and classrooms.</p><p name=\"ce41\" id=\"ce41\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-indent: -0.4em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">â€œI walk through my community and see amazing prosperity on its edges,â€ says Dennice Barr, a longtime resident and activist, sitting at a local coffee shop. â€œNone of that is for us.â€</p><p name=\"ef69\" id=\"ef69\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Despite its hardships, the Fruit Belt is still a living community, a place where neighbors call out good morning and grandparents survey the kids from front stoops. Some of the homes here date back to the 1840s, when German Lutherans founded this 36-block neighborhood and planted roots on streets with names like Orange and Lemon, giving the neighborhood its name. Today, the houses are interspersed with playgrounds, a charter school, five Baptist churches, and the incongruous, scaled-down suburban homes the city demolitions. Barrâ€™s own family moved in more than 70 years ago, part of a wave of black families lured from southern states by jobs at Bethlehem Steel or bulldozed out of Buffaloâ€™s other East Side neighborhoods.</p>', 'Â built in the 1980s and 1990s to backfill', 2, 'Published'),
(23, 'PHP5', 'the Fruit Belt ceded several blocks of residential land ', 'Tarik', '2019-03-19 05:58:24', 'upload/LoveImg.jpg', '<p name=\"9b38\" id=\"9b38\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin-top: 38px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">But in the 1950s and 60s, the Fruit Belt ceded several blocks of residential land to the expansion of Buffalo General Hospital and the Roswell Park Cancer Institute. (Housing conditions made the Fruit Belt â€œeligible for clearance,â€ city planners wrote in 1964.) Throughout the 1980s and 1990s, development officials dreamed of reviving Buffaloâ€™s downtown by expanding the two hospitals. Their vision was realized in 2001 when a clique of politicians, planners, and health care executives began plotting a research corridor called the Buffalo Niagara Medical Campus and anchored, in part, by the University at Buffalo.</p><p name=\"d26d\" id=\"d26d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Even in those early days, the campus unsettled Fruit Belt residents who thought it might undermine the neighborhood. Their concern was well-founded. Buffaloâ€™s white mayor at the time, Anthony Masiello, crowed that the development would â€œchange the face, economically and residentially, of several neighborhoods.â€</p><p name=\"4511\" id=\"4511\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Sure enough, developers tore down low-income townhouses and bought out a nearby African-American cultural center to make way for new apartments and medical offices. Worse, some residents reported rent hikes of as much as 50 percent, and one in three homes sat vacant and unusedâ€Šâ€”â€Ša common sign that owners planned to resell them at a higher price.</p><p name=\"3479\" id=\"3479\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">: â€œIt is overwhelmingly good news that property values are rising around the burgeoning Buffalo Niagara Medical Campus,â€&nbsp;<a href=\"https://buffalonews.com/2014/03/17/help-for-homeowners-shouldnt-stand-in-the-way-of-fruit-belts-renewal/\" data-href=\"https://buffalonews.com/2014/03/17/help-for-homeowners-shouldnt-stand-in-the-way-of-fruit-belts-renewal/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">an editorial</a>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot;, &quot;salt&quot;;\">Buffalo News</em>&nbsp;read. â€œThe Fruit Belt area is becoming interesting,â€ it continued, to new investors and residents.</p>', 'City power brokers cheered the trend', 4, 'Published'),
(25, 'JAVASCRIPT', 'the Medical Campus loomedâ€Šâ€”â€Šquite literally', 'manaor', '2019-03-19 06:01:43', 'upload/shutterstock-1180883800.png', '<h4 style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-indent: -0.4em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"England Hand DB\" style=\"\" size=\"5\"><font color=\"#33ccff\" style=\"\">City power brokers cheered the trend</font><span style=\"color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">: â€œIt is overwhelmingly good news that property values are rising around the burgeoning Buffalo Niagara Medical Campus,â€&nbsp;<a href=\"https://buffalonews.com/2014/03/17/help-for-homeowners-shouldnt-stand-in-the-way-of-fruit-belts-renewal/\" data-href=\"https://buffalonews.com/2014/03/17/help-for-homeowners-shouldnt-stand-in-the-way-of-fruit-belts-renewal/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px); background-color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">an editorial</a>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot;, &quot;salt&quot;;\">Buffalo News</em>&nbsp;read. â€œThe Fruit Belt area is becoming interesting,â€ it continued, to new investors and residents.<br></span></font><font face=\"England Hand DB\" size=\"5\">But to people who grew up around the Fruit Belt, like Lott and Barr, the news was mixed. Their families had fought to buy these houses and maintain their neighborhood over decades of neglect by the city. Now it seemed they might be usurped by the Fruit Beltâ€™s changing fortunes. Henry Taylor, a professor of urban planning at the University at Buffalo who developed a strategic plan for the renewal of the Fruit Belt in the early 2000s, found himself incited to regular â€œshouting matchesâ€ with his colleagues who consulted on the Medical Campus.<br></font><font face=\"England Hand DB\" style=\"\" size=\"5\">â€œWhat weâ€™ve seen in the Fruit Belt is what I call type 2 gentrification,â€ Taylor says. â€œType 1 is where whites move in and blacks and other groups are forced out. But thereâ€™s also type 2, where low-income blacks are pushed out through a process of land speculation and institutional <b style=\"\">development</b>.â€</font></h4>', 'none', 5, 'Draft'),
(26, 'PHP5', 'Organize the Content Moderators', 'manoar', '2019-03-20 13:15:40', 'upload/Untitled-1.png', '<p name=\"cfe1\" id=\"cfe1\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\"><b>Some companies are worse than others</b> â€” Uberâ€™s business model&nbsp;<a href=\"https://jacobinmag.com/2018/09/uber-misclassification-gig-economy-taxi-workers-alliance\" data-href=\"https://jacobinmag.com/2018/09/uber-misclassification-gig-economy-taxi-workers-alliance\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">boils down to</a>flouting regulations and a race to the bottom for worker pay, for example â€” but direct employees of all big tech firms are slotted into a hierarchy of pay, privileges, and status, and ever larger parts of these companiesâ€™ duties are outsourced to third-party contractors. Security officers, cafeteria workers, custodial staff, shuttle drivers â€” theyâ€™re toiling for Facebook or Google or Apple, but theyâ€™re technically employees of a subcontractor. Risk, minimized; responsibility, externalized.</font></p><p name=\"a174\" id=\"a174\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">One of the fastest growing classes of subcontracted workers are the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/your-speech-their-rules-meet-the-people-who-guard-the-internet-ab58fe6b9231\" data-href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/your-speech-their-rules-meet-the-people-who-guard-the-internet-ab58fe6b9231\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">content moderators</a>&nbsp;tasked with tending to what has too often become an unwieldy spigot of porn, child abuse, and, as tragically was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/03/18/inside-youtubes-struggles-shut-down-video-new-zealand-shooting-humans-who-outsmarted-its-systems/\" data-href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/03/18/inside-youtubes-struggles-shut-down-video-new-zealand-shooting-humans-who-outsmarted-its-systems/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">the case</a><a href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/eve7w7/documents-show-how-facebook-moderates-terrorism-on-livestreams\" data-href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/eve7w7/documents-show-how-facebook-moderates-terrorism-on-livestreams\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">&nbsp;last week</a>, a live-streamed mass shooting.</font></p><blockquote name=\"8bec\" id=\"8bec\" class=\"graf graf--pullquote graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 55px; margin-bottom: 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); border: none; padding: 0px 0px 0px 50px; --x-height-multiplier:0.342; --baseline-multiplier:0.22; font-style: italic; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.48; letter-spacing: -0.012em; text-indent: -0.32em;\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">â€œFacebook as a whole respects the right of our partner employees to organize.â€</font></blockquote><p name=\"6caf\" id=\"6caf\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--pullquote\" style=\"margin-top: 54px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">Content moderators â€œneed something much more fundamental than a campaign to join a traditional American labor union,â€ says Eric Murphy, a security officer on Facebookâ€™s main campus. Murphy, like thousands of his fellow subcontracted tech workers in the United States, recently unionized (the security guards&nbsp;<a href=\"https://gizmodo.com/after-five-years-of-fighting-google-and-facebook-secur-1828304237\" data-href=\"https://gizmodo.com/after-five-years-of-fighting-google-and-facebook-secur-1828304237\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">joined the Service Employees International Union</a>, or SEIU), but the growing army of moderators â€” around&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-02-25/facebook-grappling-with-employee-anger-over-moderator-conditions\" data-href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-02-25/facebook-grappling-with-employee-anger-over-moderator-conditions\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">15,000 for Facebook alone</a> â€” has yet to join that wave. Theyâ€™re the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/my-awful-life-as-the-internets-janitor\" data-href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/my-awful-life-as-the-internets-janitor\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">janitors of the internet</a>, low-paid workers who scrub these platforms to make them look a bit more like the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/whatsapp-wont-solve-the-facebook-problems-you-worry-about-24e21e8fdcb4\" data-href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/whatsapp-wont-solve-the-facebook-problems-you-worry-about-24e21e8fdcb4\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">immaculate visions</a>&nbsp;conjured by their executives.</font></p><p name=\"d229\" id=\"d229\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-indent: -0.4em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">â€œMaybe if Mark Zuckerberg had to do the job for a week, he would have some ideas about how to fix it,â€ Murphy notes.</font></p><p name=\"07f7\" id=\"07f7\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">Many subcontracted workers who labor on or near tech campuses see the industryâ€™s immense wealth up close every day, and they view the widespread practice of subcontracting as a way to keep them from accessing it. As&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nplusonemag.com/issue-31/politics/code-red/\" data-href=\"https://nplusonemag.com/issue-31/politics/code-red/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">Murphy told me</a>&nbsp;last year, â€œMy coworkers and I dream about going direct with Facebook: Thatâ€™s where the money is, thatâ€™s where the power is, and this artifice of subcontracting is just a scheme to hold down our wages and prevent us from getting a whack at the Facebook piÃ±ata.â€</font></p><p name=\"726d\" id=\"726d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\"><b>Content moderators,</b> by contrast, operate in relative isolation, hidden away from gleaming Silicon Valley campuses, their existence downplayed by executives who&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/27/18242724/facebook-moderation-ai-artificial-intelligence-platforms\" data-href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/27/18242724/facebook-moderation-ai-artificial-intelligence-platforms\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">tout A.I.â€™s role in moderation</a>, even as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/xwk9zd/how-facebook-content-moderation-works\" data-href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/xwk9zd/how-facebook-content-moderation-works\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">human beings do much</a>of the heavy lifting.</font></p>', 'the,content,creator', 0, 'Published'),
(28, 'PHP5', 'pornography so it can be removed before reaching Facebook users.', 'tarik', '2019-03-20 13:20:58', 'upload/oE7rYRe.jpg', '<p name=\"e811\" id=\"e811\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><a href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/why-conspiracy-theories-work-so-well-on-facebook-466a42af6b76\" data-href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/why-conspiracy-theories-work-so-well-on-facebook-466a42af6b76\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">Psychological trauma</a>&nbsp;is rampant among the workers. Cognizant reportedly offers health care and â€œwellness timeâ€ to the workers, but this is limited to nine minutes per shift and is policed viciously. (Workers are ordered not to use wellness time to go to the restroom, according to Newtonâ€™s story). Cognizant stresses the availability of counselors for workers in need of help â€” a point&nbsp;<a href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/43z7gj/how-facebook-trains-content-moderators\" data-href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/43z7gj/how-facebook-trains-content-moderators\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">Facebook has talked up</a>&nbsp;in the recent past â€” but at least some of the counselors appear to be less than helpful. One of them told Newton of the concept of â€œâ€˜post-traumatic growth,â€™ an effect whereby some trauma victims emerge from the experience feeling stronger than before.â€</p><p name=\"422d\" id=\"422d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Moderators need to get organized and quickly. The work is by its nature unpleasant, but the first step toward decent working conditions requires moderators, collectively and without fear of retaliation, to be able to state the problems most pressing to them and how they think those issues can be resolved. Should their employers or Facebook itself decline to implement these fixes, the moderators could then decide how to force them to do so. Unions representing other subcontractors at Facebook â€” <a href=\"https://unitehere.org/press-releases/cafeteria-workers-at-facebook-vote-for-first-union-contract/\" data-href=\"https://unitehere.org/press-releases/cafeteria-workers-at-facebook-vote-for-first-union-contract/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">Unite Here</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mercurynews.com/2018/06/15/these-are-poverty-level-jobs-in-facebook-silicon-valley-security-officers-protest-for-better-wages/\" data-href=\"https://www.mercurynews.com/2018/06/15/these-are-poverty-level-jobs-in-facebook-silicon-valley-security-officers-protest-for-better-wages/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">SEIU</a>, and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://observer.com/2017/04/teamsters-facebook-google-linkedin/\" data-href=\"https://observer.com/2017/04/teamsters-facebook-google-linkedin/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">Teamsters</a>&nbsp;in the case of Facebookâ€™s shuttle drivers â€” might be best positioned to assist them.</p><p name=\"27f7\" id=\"27f7\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Asked if Facebook would take a position on organization among content moderators, a spokesperson said, â€œFacebook as a whole respects the right of our partner employees to organize.â€ But thereâ€™s been no public effort yet by moderators within the U.S. to organize.</p><p name=\"bfbc\" id=\"bfbc\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Direct employees of platforms like Facebook or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/3/13/17117554/youtube-content-moderators-limit-four-hours-sxsw\" data-href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/3/13/17117554/youtube-content-moderators-limit-four-hours-sxsw\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">YouTube</a>&nbsp;have a role to play by advocating for subcontracted moderators. Doing so would help build alliances across the vast blue- and white-collar divide in tech, a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.thenation.com/article/tech-workers-google-facebook-protest-dsa/\" data-href=\"https://www.thenation.com/article/tech-workers-google-facebook-protest-dsa/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">priority</a>&nbsp;of recent&nbsp;<a href=\"https://newrepublic.com/article/153046/stark-political-divide-tech-ceos-employees\" data-href=\"https://newrepublic.com/article/153046/stark-political-divide-tech-ceos-employees\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">tech worker organizing</a>. â€œTechies should absolutely be using their privileged positions to advocate for the people that their company is exploiting â€” and, in this case, arguably torturing â€” because they benefit from that exploitation,â€ Murphy says.</p><p name=\"425d\" id=\"425d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Judging by Facebookâ€™s response to the&nbsp;<em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot;, &quot;salt&quot;;\">Verge&nbsp;</em>investigation, the company isnâ€™t planning to restructure its model anytime soon. Justin Osofsky, Facebookâ€™s vice president of global operations, emailed Facebook employees, then&nbsp;<a href=\"https://newsroom.fb.com/news/2019/02/commitment-to-content-reviewers/\" data-href=\"https://newsroom.fb.com/news/2019/02/commitment-to-content-reviewers/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">published the message</a>&nbsp;online. The post emphasized the speed at which the company is scaling up its moderation operation â€” it has â€œmore than doubledâ€ in each of the past two years. The majority of these workers are employed by staffing firms like Cognizant as well as Accenture and Genpact. Osofsky wrote of a summit with its vendors planned for April of â€œimproved partner support and communicationsâ€ â€” encouraging workers to raise concerns with human resources or anonymously via a whistleblower hotline â€” as well as further compliance auditing and contract standardization.</p><blockquote name=\"5ae6\" id=\"5ae6\" class=\"graf graf--pullquote graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 55px; margin-bottom: 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); border: none; padding: 0px 0px 0px 50px; --x-height-multiplier:0.342; --baseline-multiplier:0.22; font-family: medium-content-slab-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.48; letter-spacing: -0.012em; text-indent: -0.32em;\">â€œThese workers are doing the social-care work that we never treat as valuable in our culture.â€</blockquote><div><br></div>', 'These workers are doing the', 2, 'Published');

